50|$|Many {{species of}} marine mammals {{are found in}} Barrow Canyon {{throughout}} the year. As offshore sea ice melts, Pacific walrus rely on coastal habitat for haulouts and on the region’s rich seafloor for foraging. Beluga <b>whales,</b> <b>polar</b> bears, bowhead <b>whales,</b> and several species of seals, including spotted seals, bearded seals, and ringed seals, also rely on this region as an important feeding area. Gray whales cluster {{at the mouth of}} Barrow Canyon where there are large concentrations of zooplankton.|$|R
