5000|$|Sir Walter William [...] "Wally" [...] Herbert (24 October 1934 - 12 June 2007) was a British polar explorer, {{writer and}} artist. In 1969 {{he became the}} first man fully {{recognized}} for walking to the North Pole, on the 60th anniversary of Robert Peary's famous, but disputed, expedition. He was described by Sir Ranulph Fiennes as [...] "the <b>greatest</b> <b>polar</b> explorer of our time".|$|R
